data.enText: a woman who is not married, especially an older woman who is not likely to marry

data.text: This word should not now be used to mean simply a woman who is not married.
如今，不可用这个单词泛指未婚女子。

data.chText: 从前，就多数妇女而言，结婚的比独身的更有地位。
data.enText: For most women, marriage used to bring a higher status than spinsterhood.

simple_means.memory_skill: spin 纺纱 + ster …人 → 为自己纺婚纱 → 未婚少女

tr: someone who spins (who twists fibers into threads)

value.def: A spinster is a woman who has never been married; used especially when talking about an old or middle-aged woman.
value.tran: (老)处女;未婚中年(或老年)女子
